With the end of the Cold War, the U.N. is playing an

It has led efforts to end civil wars in El Salvador and Cambodia, and it also helped monitor elections in Namibia.
During the 1980s, when the Reagan administration drew the line against communist-backed insurgences in Central America, Mr. Pickering played an active role in that effort as U.S. envoy to El Salvador.
Mr. Perkins was the U.S. ambassador to South Africa in 1986, when the U.S. imposed economic sanctions against that nation's white-minority government to pressure it to end apartheid.
Mr. Pickering, reached over the weekend, refused to comment on his future plans, and Mr. Perkins couldn't be reached.
